          "backend/deploy_access_ext.py"
        ],
        "reviewed_at": "2026-06-15T01:35:57.709572+00:00",
        "second_opinion": {
          "verdict": "do_not_ship",
          "summary": "Hardcoded JWT secret in production code is a critical security vulnerability that must be fixed before shipping.",
          "concerns": [
            "JWT_SECRET defaults to 'change-me' in auth_utils.py \u2014 this is a critical security flaw if deployed to production without env var override",
            "No .env.example or deployment docs warning operators to set JWT_SECRET \u2014 easy to ship with the default",
            "auto_fix_max_iterations hard-capped at 5 but autopilot.py lacks rate-limiting on the auto-fix loop \u2014 a malicious actor could spam deploy attempts",
            "deploy/auto_fix module imported but not shown \u2014 cannot verify the GitHub commit flow is safe from injection attacks",
            "ai_learnings_auto.py calls LLM with user content but no mention of input sanitization before storage \u2014 XSS risk if learnings render as HTML",
            "alerts_ext.py webhook URLs stored in plaintext settings doc \u2014 no encryption at rest for secrets"
          ],
          "reviewer_model": "claude-sonnet-4-5"
        },
